
Vault Prod Setup(1st time):
Install vault for Windows-64 bit
Execute the commands in windows cmd(Admin)

cd C:\Program Files\vault(your vault path)

vault.exe server -config=config.hcl -address="127.0.0.1:8200"

set VAULT_ADDR=http://localhost:8200

vault.exe status 

vault.exe operator init 
**Important** The above command will return the 5 Unseal keys and the Root Token. This is the only time the keys will be available to be seen. So, store them safely.

vault.exe operator unseal *unseal key*

vault.exe operator unseal *unseal key*

vault.exe operator unseal *unseal key* 

vault.exe login root_token

vault.exe audit enable -path="vault_audit" file file_path="/Program Files/vault/vault_audit.log"

vault.exe auth enable okta

vault.exe write auth/okta/config base_url="okta.com" org_name="dev-******" api_token="*****************"

optional:
vault.exe login -method=okta username=user@company.com password=*******

Vault Prod Server is setup!!
